# TYPING RULE: const-generic argument reference must resolve to a declared
# const parameter of matching name on the enclosing impl.
#
# Prior art: RFC 2000 ("Const generics") — a const-generic argument slot
# (the `<N>` in `Type<N>`) must be filled either by a constant expression
# whose type matches the declared const parameter's type, or by an in-scope
# const-generic parameter identifier of that same declared type; an
# argument naming an identifier that is not actually a declared const
# parameter in scope is a name-resolution/typing error (rustc E0412/E0425
# territory — "cannot find value/type in this scope" — depending on
# context). This rule checks the "names an in-scope declared const
# parameter" half specifically (gec:argConstIsParamRef true), since that is
# the only const-generic argument FORM in this corpus that references a
# parameter rather than a literal.
#
# ggen template pattern this checks:
#   packs/tcps-core-pack/ontology.ttl:200
#   `impl<const 上限: usize> 系譜台帳<上限> { ... }` — gec:Impl_系譜台帳_constN.
#   The type argument `上限` inside `系譜台帳<上限>` (gec:argConstIsParamRef
#   true, gec:argConstValue "上限") must resolve to the impl's own declared
#   `const 上限: usize` (gec:ConstGenericParam, gec:paramName "上限") — and it
#   does. (The corpus's other const-generic instance,
#   `作業領域::<3>::新規()` — lib.rs.tmpl:45, gec:Local_作業領域 — is a literal
#   argument, gec:argConstIsParamRef unset/false, so it is out of this
#   rule's scope by design: literals have no name to resolve.)
#
# Verified 2026-07-21: ASK=false against ontology.ttl+fixtures/gec-facts.ttl
# (系譜台帳's `上限` argument correctly resolves to its own declared const
# param); ASK=true against an adversarial fixture asserting a const-generic
# argument referencing a name ("NOT_DECLARED") that is not among the
# enclosing impl's declared gec:ConstGenericParam individuals.
PREFIX gec: <http://seanchatmangpt.github.io/packs/rust-dialect#>
ASK {
  ?impl a ?implType ; gec:forType ?ft .
  VALUES ?implType { gec:TraitImpl gec:InherentImpl }
  ?ft (gec:hasArgument/gec:argType)* ?anyGT .
  ?anyGT a gec:GenericType ; gec:hasArgument ?arg .
  ?arg a gec:TypeArgumentConst ; gec:argConstIsParamRef true ; gec:argConstValue ?refName .
  FILTER NOT EXISTS {
    ?impl gec:genericParam ?cgp .
    ?cgp a gec:ConstGenericParam ; gec:paramName ?refName .
  }
}
